        "text": "Proverbs 16:28",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Proverbs 10:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). This is the culminating point in the character of the wicked man. He takes delight in breaking up friendship and in destroying concord among brethren (see ver. 19), and thus destroys one of the most essential elements for promoting individual happiness and the welfare of the community at large. This idea of the community is introduced into the LXX., which reads, \"Such an one brings disturbance to the city (",
